LOGO DESIGN BRIEF (MINIMALIST STYLE – CAFE BRAND)

1. Project Overview
We are looking for a freelance designer to create a modern, minimalist logo for a café brand. The logo should be clean, stylish, and memorable, reflecting a cozy yet contemporary atmosphere.

2. About the Brand

Brand name: Quiet Cup
Industry: Café / Coffee Shop / Food & Beverage
Description: A modern café focused on high-quality coffee, simple food, and a relaxed atmosphere.
Core values: Simplicity, comfort, quality, authenticity

3. Target Audience

Age: 20–45
Location: Urban / city-based customers
Audience profile:
Young professionals
Students
Creative individuals / freelancers
Brand perception: cozy, modern, aesthetic, slightly premium but approachable

4. Design Requirements

Style: Minimalist, clean, modern
Preferred logo type:
Combination mark (icon + text) or wordmark
Visual direction:
Subtle café-related elements (e.g., cup, bean, steam, abstract shapes)
Use of negative space is highly appreciated
Avoid clichés and overly detailed illustrations
Color palette:
Primary: neutral tones (black, white, beige, warm gray)
Accent: muted natural tones (e.g., brown, olive, terracotta)
Typography:
Clean sans-serif or elegant serif (modern feel)

5. Deliverables
The designer should provide:

2–3 initial logo concepts
Up to 2 revision rounds
Final files in: AI, EPS, SVG, PNG, JPG
Variations:
Full logo
Icon-only version (for cups, social media, signage)
Black & white and color versions
Transparent background
Optional: basic brand guidelines (spacing, colors, fonts)

6. Usage
The logo will be used on:

Coffee cups and packaging
Signage (outdoor & indoor)
Social media and website
Menus and printed materials

The design must remain clear and recognizable in small sizes and on physical items.

7. Timeline

First concepts: 3–5 business days
Final delivery: within 7–10 days

8. Budget

Fixed price: $120–$350
Payment terms:
50% upfront
50% after final delivery

9. Requirements for the Designer

Experience in branding for cafés, restaurants, or lifestyle brands
Strong portfolio with minimalist designs
Understanding of how logos work on physical products (cups, signs)
Good communication and adherence to deadlines

10. Additional Notes
The logo should feel warm and inviting while remaining simple and modern. It should be versatile enough to work across both digital and physical environments. We are looking for a distinctive identity, not a generic coffee logo.
